WEBVTT

00:06.833 --> 00:09.542
-[guards grunting]
-[Daredevil grunting, yelling]

00:11.792 --> 00:14.500
[Matt] That boat was full of weapons,
launchers and rifles.

00:14.583 --> 00:16.667
He's using the Freeport to smuggle arms.

00:16.750 --> 00:18.458
[Sheila] The wreck's
blocking the entrance.

00:18.542 --> 00:20.875
Nothing is landing till
the Northern Star's cleared.

00:20.958 --> 00:22.333
This is a terrorist attack.

00:22.417 --> 00:25.625
The hunt for Daredevil,
Karen Page. Intensify it.

00:25.708 --> 00:29.458
The people I work for
are grateful for the use of your port.

00:29.542 --> 00:32.500
But this has gone into,
like, eight kinds of wrong.

00:32.583 --> 00:34.958
There's an email on this card.

00:35.042 --> 00:37.250
Not everything I write is under my name.

00:37.667 --> 00:39.542
[Fisk] I imagine that you know

00:39.625 --> 00:42.458
who in my staff is loyal and who is not.

00:42.542 --> 00:45.167
-[gun cocks and fires]
-[people screaming]

00:45.250 --> 00:47.542
Achilleo and Christofi
are in a lot of trouble.

00:47.625 --> 00:48.833
Task Force took him.

00:48.917 --> 00:49.917
Where's Christofi?

00:50.000 --> 00:51.167
[Achilleo] I don't know.

00:51.250 --> 00:52.417
-[gun fires]
-[groans]

00:53.167 --> 00:55.333
-[man] Sorry about your client, Murdock.
-[Matt] Me too.

00:55.417 --> 00:56.833
They killed him. The police.

00:56.917 --> 00:59.250
-I'm sorry.
-I hate them, Mister Murdock.

01:01.500 --> 01:02.625
[grunting]

01:02.708 --> 01:04.333
[shallow breathing]

01:08.458 --> 01:10.958
[gasps, breathing heavily]

01:18.500 --> 01:19.792
[spray paint can rattles]

01:25.333 --> 01:27.708
[sirens wailing in distance]

02:11.708 --> 02:14.125
[sirens wailing]

02:40.333 --> 02:41.667
Can I help you?

02:48.833 --> 02:49.833
Can I help you?

02:51.083 --> 02:52.750
[Dex] There a nun who works here?

02:52.833 --> 02:55.250
Sister Maggie, I think.

02:55.833 --> 02:58.750
[man] Yes, she's on a sabbatical year
in Rome.

03:00.333 --> 03:01.333
[Dex] Father, I--

03:03.292 --> 03:05.042
I need absolution.

03:06.542 --> 03:08.125
I've betrayed people.

03:09.458 --> 03:11.042
I've betrayed myself.

03:11.833 --> 03:12.833
[man] Oh, uh...

03:13.375 --> 03:15.333
I'm not technically a priest yet.

03:15.417 --> 03:17.875
I can't administer
the sacrament of Penance, but...

03:20.417 --> 03:21.875
I'm not too picky.

03:29.125 --> 03:32.625
One. One-two. One-two.
One-two. One-two, slip.

03:32.708 --> 03:34.917
-Body.
-[both grunting]

03:35.000 --> 03:36.000
Time!

03:36.083 --> 03:37.667
[Fisk panting]

03:37.750 --> 03:39.292
Sir, I need to talk to you.

03:40.083 --> 03:41.083
What happened?

03:41.667 --> 03:43.625
The cop in Hell's Kitchen.

03:44.208 --> 03:45.583
Daredevil was there.

03:46.333 --> 03:48.042
Thirty-second break. No more.

03:48.542 --> 03:50.417
Gotta get you ready for fight night.

03:50.833 --> 03:52.125
The cop's in hospital.

03:52.208 --> 03:55.000
-Good.
-Well, he had a heart attack.

03:56.000 --> 03:58.417
Four Task Force, dead.

03:58.792 --> 04:00.333
Daredevil got away.

04:00.833 --> 04:02.958
Apparently, someone is helping him.

04:03.583 --> 04:05.333
Someone with very good aim.

04:07.333 --> 04:08.583
Poindexter.

04:09.250 --> 04:11.458
[trainer] You giving up?
Not like you, man.

04:11.833 --> 04:13.083
Not like you at all.

04:13.167 --> 04:14.875
I thought you were tougher than that.

04:14.958 --> 04:17.458
-[Fisk yelling]
-[trainer groans]

04:20.792 --> 04:22.792
[♪ theme music playing]

06:00.833 --> 06:02.667
[vehicle horns blaring]

06:02.750 --> 06:04.208
Okay. Thank you.

06:05.625 --> 06:07.458
Cherry's stable at Metro General.

06:09.042 --> 06:11.167
But the Task Force
can still get to him there.

06:11.625 --> 06:13.000
Yeah, I'll get eyes on him.

06:13.708 --> 06:15.250
Why was Bullseye even there?

06:15.333 --> 06:16.333
I don't know.

06:17.083 --> 06:18.417
He could have killed me.

06:18.500 --> 06:20.167
-Like the Task Force.
-But he didn't.

06:20.250 --> 06:21.250
So, what is that?

06:21.333 --> 06:23.500
Is he just crazy,
or does he have a reason?

06:23.917 --> 06:26.417
Well, killing Task Force
only helps Fisk. Right?

06:26.500 --> 06:27.958
He's saying I'm a terrorist.

06:28.042 --> 06:30.917
So, each body Poindexter drops
is just another hung on me.

06:31.000 --> 06:34.125
Yeah. And it pisses off Fisk.
So that's like two birds, one bullet.

06:34.208 --> 06:36.958
Right. But he doesn't want me dead.

06:38.583 --> 06:40.458
I don't give a shit. He killed Foggy.

06:41.125 --> 06:43.792
I hope those Task Force psychos
put a bullet in his head.

06:43.875 --> 06:47.000
-Karen, that's not helping.
-Yeah? Well, I imagine you feel the same.

06:49.042 --> 06:50.208
Thank you.

06:51.375 --> 06:55.625
Poindexter aside, I want to take down Fisk
before there's any more collateral damage.

06:56.333 --> 06:57.333
Okay, um...

06:57.958 --> 07:00.292
-We prove the Mayor was smuggling guns.
-Right.

07:00.375 --> 07:02.208
-Try and get the feds to file a case.
-Mmm-hmm.

07:02.292 --> 07:05.375
-That at least gets him out of City Hall.
-We can hope.

07:05.458 --> 07:09.333
The Task Force shook down Cherry
once they found Northern Star's captain,

07:09.417 --> 07:11.625
which means
the First Mate's still out there.

07:11.708 --> 07:13.500
-We need to get to Ariana.
-Hell yeah.

07:13.583 --> 07:15.875
So, which one of us is going to Astoria?

07:16.458 --> 07:17.458
How about both?

07:18.417 --> 07:20.083
[people chattering]

07:22.667 --> 07:24.792
[officer 1] Boots on the ground! Now!

07:27.625 --> 07:29.250
[officer 2] Suspect! Hands up!

07:35.542 --> 07:37.417
-[man 1] They're takin' her.
-[woman] Seriously?

07:37.500 --> 07:39.458
[man 2] Yo, what'd she do?
Hey, what'd she do?

07:39.542 --> 07:41.458
-What y'all doin'?
-[officer 3] In the truck.

07:41.542 --> 07:43.208
-Now!
-[woman] Don't do that to her.

07:43.292 --> 07:44.833
-[man 3] Come on.
-[chatter continues]

07:46.042 --> 07:47.042
[Buck] If I may...

07:47.917 --> 07:49.292
[clicks tongue]

07:49.375 --> 07:50.458
...add a thought...

07:52.958 --> 07:54.125
about Daredevil.

07:55.458 --> 07:59.042
You know, you would have
much more influence over the situation

07:59.125 --> 08:01.500
if you let it be known that he

08:02.125 --> 08:03.458
and Matt Murdock...

08:04.000 --> 08:05.333
are one and the same.

08:09.292 --> 08:10.458
No.

08:10.542 --> 08:11.542
No.

08:13.583 --> 08:16.333
I want to quash this idiocy, not stoke it.

08:16.833 --> 08:20.833
Daredevil, he's an easy sell
as enemy of the people,

08:20.917 --> 08:22.708
but Matt Murdock? No, I--

08:23.167 --> 08:26.625
A blind man who saved my life?

08:26.708 --> 08:27.708
I don't think so.

08:29.750 --> 08:31.208
He saved my life.

08:36.792 --> 08:37.833
[cameraman] Slating.

08:37.917 --> 08:39.875
Take... Set.

08:40.750 --> 08:43.333
And... whenever you're ready,
Mister Mayor.

08:44.250 --> 08:47.292
As you know, months ago,
there was an attempt on my life

08:48.042 --> 08:51.375
by the masked vigilante known as Bullseye.

08:52.458 --> 08:54.625
We have reason to believe
that Matt Murdock,

08:55.083 --> 08:56.667
the lawyer from Hell's Kitchen,

08:57.000 --> 08:59.250
survived the attack on his apartment.

09:00.458 --> 09:01.958
This is important...

09:03.417 --> 09:05.417
because Matt Murdock is...

09:10.458 --> 09:11.542
a hero.

09:12.250 --> 09:14.292
[cell phone vibrating]

09:14.375 --> 09:16.792
He risked his life to save mine...

09:18.167 --> 09:20.500
only to be targeted by the same vigilantes

09:20.583 --> 09:22.708
that threaten our way of life.

09:23.125 --> 09:24.542
He could be hurt.

09:25.250 --> 09:26.875
He may not know who he is.

09:26.958 --> 09:28.792
We need to get you out of here. Now.

09:28.875 --> 09:31.500
Help find Matt Murdock, New York.

09:32.125 --> 09:33.958
Let's bring this hero home.

09:38.833 --> 09:40.667
[BB Urich] What do you think
of the Northern Star?

09:40.750 --> 09:42.292
[woman] That boat capsized in the river?

09:42.375 --> 09:44.000
What a mess. How do they fix that?

09:44.083 --> 09:46.375
I don't know.
If you ask me, Daredevil did it.

09:46.750 --> 09:48.875
Or one of those other crazies.

09:48.958 --> 09:51.125
This resistance with the graffiti.

09:51.208 --> 09:52.708
What are they resisting?

09:52.792 --> 09:54.917
New York's never been
this good in 30 years.

09:55.000 --> 09:56.708
[♪ jaunty music playing on tablet]

09:56.792 --> 09:58.958
[Kingpin] Uh-oh!
Looks like I spoke too soon.

09:59.083 --> 10:00.167
Someone caught me.

10:00.250 --> 10:03.208
Spoiled again by that dastardly do-gooder.

10:03.292 --> 10:04.708
I'll get him in the end.

10:04.792 --> 10:06.792
-[Sheila] Has the Mayor seen this?
-I don't know.

10:06.875 --> 10:09.167
I mean, it's pretty underground, you know.

10:09.250 --> 10:11.917
But these drops, they show up on socials,

10:12.000 --> 10:13.000
then they disappear.

10:13.083 --> 10:14.250
It's like guerrilla shit.

10:14.333 --> 10:15.458
Let me rephrase that.

10:15.875 --> 10:18.125
Are you going to show it to the Mayor?

10:18.208 --> 10:21.083
Yeah, I probably should,
but he's not gonna like that mask.

10:21.167 --> 10:22.625
No, he's not.

10:22.708 --> 10:25.208
These blips, they're unsubstantiated.

10:25.708 --> 10:27.333
They're only rumor, right?

10:27.833 --> 10:30.917
The Bulletin, the other majors,
they're not picking it up.

10:31.000 --> 10:32.458
We shouldn't give it any oxygen.

10:32.542 --> 10:34.708
Who else had access to this footage?

10:35.542 --> 10:37.500
Buck, you, Fisk.

10:38.000 --> 10:39.458
Probably Powell.

10:40.542 --> 10:42.875
-You?
-Yeah, me.

10:42.958 --> 10:44.375
Is it on your laptop?

10:44.458 --> 10:45.917
Hell no.

10:46.625 --> 10:48.125
I wouldn't do that, Sheila.

10:48.583 --> 10:50.292
-Come on.
-Show it to him.

10:50.917 --> 10:53.333
He's not a fan of surprises.

10:53.750 --> 10:56.250
But let's be honest,
this is not just bad PR,

10:56.333 --> 10:58.333
and it's coming from inside this building.

10:58.417 --> 10:59.917
Tracked the "at." Dark web.

11:00.000 --> 11:01.125
It's just a leak.

11:01.208 --> 11:02.833
Find it, plug it, and we move on.

11:02.917 --> 11:04.083
It's gonna be okay.

11:04.167 --> 11:05.583
Thanks. Sheila?

11:06.208 --> 11:08.333
Look, I-- I know I can be an ass.

11:08.417 --> 11:10.208
I know we've had our differences, but...

11:11.333 --> 11:14.292
-I really do respect your advice.
-I appreciate that, bubba.

11:15.042 --> 11:16.917
Just try and take it once in a while?

11:17.000 --> 11:18.625
[indistinct chatter outside]

11:24.542 --> 11:25.708
[exhales heavily]

11:25.792 --> 11:27.208
Fuck me.

11:28.208 --> 11:29.458
[Matt] Kind of brilliant, right?

11:30.417 --> 11:31.542
Fisk not outing me?

11:33.083 --> 11:34.083
This way,

11:34.708 --> 11:37.792
he gets all the people
who support vigilantes

11:37.875 --> 11:40.208
searching for Matt Murdock
and their haters

11:40.292 --> 11:41.500
searching for Daredevil.

11:41.750 --> 11:43.375
[Karen] Yeah, well... [breathing heavily]

11:43.458 --> 11:45.250
You're wanted by both sides now.

11:47.333 --> 11:48.875
[chuckles softly] Huh...

11:49.667 --> 11:52.917
[Powell] So we tripled the security
personnel here and at Gracie.

11:53.000 --> 11:56.500
Not my call to tell you to lay low,
even with that fight next week.

11:56.583 --> 11:58.500
But when you or Mrs. Fisk are on the move,

11:58.583 --> 12:01.583
you're gonna have two full,
close protection details,

12:01.667 --> 12:03.917
and I'll volunteer
for one of them personally.

12:06.167 --> 12:09.042
I have Buck to augment my usual detail.

12:09.125 --> 12:10.958
Sure, no flies on Mr. Cashman.

12:11.417 --> 12:13.292
But, listen, Poindexter's no joke.

12:13.875 --> 12:15.792
He fired at you with 30 of us right there.

12:15.875 --> 12:18.125
You're only here
because of that prick lawyer.

12:18.208 --> 12:20.542
You're not much of
a politician, are you, Powell?

12:20.625 --> 12:21.958
I say it like I see it, sir.

12:22.583 --> 12:23.667
Well, here's to that.

12:23.750 --> 12:24.792
[glasses clink]

12:25.792 --> 12:26.958
Murdock's an asshole.

12:27.042 --> 12:29.000
You want him
treated like gold, you got it.

12:29.875 --> 12:32.208
Bullseye, if he tried once,
he'll try again.

12:32.292 --> 12:33.708
My guys know not to fuck around.

12:33.792 --> 12:35.250
They see him, they kill him.

12:35.958 --> 12:37.125
Same with Daredevil.

12:37.208 --> 12:39.042
Your dedication is impressive.

12:40.125 --> 12:43.208
No, I owe that red piece of shit
for what he did to my guys.

12:43.417 --> 12:44.708
You just want to know,

12:44.792 --> 12:46.250
if you go down like that,

12:46.333 --> 12:48.542
whether someone's
gonna get payback for you.

12:50.042 --> 12:51.583
That's just how it works, sir.

12:52.083 --> 12:53.083
Yes, it is.

12:53.750 --> 12:56.042
Murdock's friend, the ex-cop.

12:57.083 --> 12:58.542
Cherry, yeah.

12:58.625 --> 13:00.750
Yeah. I understand he's at Metro General.

13:00.833 --> 13:01.917
Yeah, I'm on it.

13:02.375 --> 13:04.042
I got a couple other things, too.

13:04.125 --> 13:06.083
I'll put Matt Murdock in this office,

13:07.000 --> 13:09.458
and I'll put Daredevil's head
on a fuckin' spike.

13:12.333 --> 13:14.167
Either of those would be sufficient.

13:15.083 --> 13:16.958
Well, I like to shoot the moon, sir.

13:20.083 --> 13:21.542
[radio beeping]

13:22.417 --> 13:24.542
[indistinct radio chatter]

13:26.333 --> 13:27.333
I just, uh...

13:32.292 --> 13:33.292
Cole.

13:34.208 --> 13:35.708
Hey, what's going on?

13:36.750 --> 13:37.958
What are you doing here?

13:39.458 --> 13:40.625
I want back in, man.

13:41.250 --> 13:43.083
I need to be back on the Task Force.

13:43.875 --> 13:44.875
Yeah.

13:45.250 --> 13:47.000
Okay. Uh...

13:47.833 --> 13:49.458
I mean... [chuckles softly]

13:50.542 --> 13:51.750
you gotta heal, man.

13:51.833 --> 13:54.125
This is as good as it's gonna get
for me, man.

13:55.125 --> 13:57.000
-Look, after what they've done?
-Yeah.

13:57.083 --> 13:58.250
-Not just to me.
-Yeah.

13:59.292 --> 14:01.292
Fuck the vigilantes.

14:01.667 --> 14:03.375
I'm owed some get-back, brother.

14:04.083 --> 14:06.417
How many people died
in that asshole lawyer's place?

14:06.500 --> 14:08.375
-Seven. Yeah, seven.
-Seven. Exactly.

14:09.583 --> 14:10.792
I'm fucking sure, man.

14:11.958 --> 14:12.958
I'm ready.

14:13.958 --> 14:15.042
Okay. Yeah.

14:15.125 --> 14:16.333
-Okay? Yeah?
-Yeah.

14:16.417 --> 14:17.958
Yeah, welcome back, brother.

14:18.375 --> 14:20.333
-Thanks. Let's get to work.
-All right.

14:20.417 --> 14:22.625
-[indistinct radio chatter]
-[radio beeping]

14:33.042 --> 14:34.708
[Bob] You guys can call it a day.

14:34.792 --> 14:36.083
Yeah,

14:36.167 --> 14:38.792
-but we were told to--
-Look, I'm telling you to get lost.

14:38.875 --> 14:41.750
It's okay. Don't do anything
and get yourself in trouble.

14:41.833 --> 14:43.917
Oh! [chuckles]

14:44.000 --> 14:45.875
What the fuck is this? Jurassic Park?

14:46.625 --> 14:48.042
Just visiting an old friend.

14:48.125 --> 14:49.125
[McDaniel] Nice vests.

14:49.208 --> 14:51.708
You gonna wear
your underwear outside, too?

14:52.250 --> 14:53.250
Get out.

14:53.333 --> 14:55.667
[indistinct announcements over PA]

14:55.750 --> 14:57.500
[monitors beeping]

14:57.583 --> 15:00.208
-We need backup.
-[McDaniel] Yeah, Danny said he'd stop in.

15:00.292 --> 15:03.042
-[Angie] Roxanne, too.
-Have her bring some Lombardi's.

15:03.125 --> 15:04.833
You know how bored these guys are?

15:05.833 --> 15:08.167
You know how many more of them
are out there?

15:13.167 --> 15:14.958
-[Bob] We'll be back.
-We'll be here.

15:15.250 --> 15:18.708
You bringing the pizza?
Or should we still have Roxanne do it?

15:20.208 --> 15:21.292
[Bob] Fuckin' hump.

15:25.333 --> 15:26.333
Dick.

15:27.042 --> 15:29.333
God, I hate those little dickheads.

15:29.417 --> 15:30.708
[chuckles softly]

15:31.500 --> 15:32.625
Remember McDaniel?

15:32.708 --> 15:34.375
Oh, yeah, I remember McDaniel.

15:35.167 --> 15:36.958
Word is, he was North's TO.

15:38.125 --> 15:39.458
-You're kidding me?
-Nope.

15:39.542 --> 15:41.542
-That explains a lot, man.
-Yeah?

15:41.625 --> 15:43.042
Hey, but don't sweat it--

15:43.125 --> 15:44.750
[elevator bell dings]

16:09.750 --> 16:11.333
[elevator bell dinging]

16:18.833 --> 16:20.917
[Powell] Fuck.
Did Cherry nose-blast the two?

16:21.458 --> 16:22.542
Fuck.

16:23.458 --> 16:25.458
You gotta be fucking-- Unbelievable.

16:25.542 --> 16:26.583
Stay.

16:30.917 --> 16:32.208
[exhales]

16:32.792 --> 16:34.250
[chuckling]

16:34.333 --> 16:35.958
[sniffles, sighs]

16:36.625 --> 16:37.875
He's fuckin' gone.

16:39.708 --> 16:42.417
[Fisk] It seems this is turning into
guerrilla warfare.

16:42.833 --> 16:43.833
[Powell] So, what is this?

16:43.917 --> 16:45.250
Is Poindexter freelancing?

16:45.333 --> 16:47.125
Or is he in this Resistance mess?

16:47.208 --> 16:49.875
Without vigilantes,
there is no Resistance.

16:50.333 --> 16:53.333
Destroy one and you destroy the other.

16:54.042 --> 16:58.583
And, Powell? Vanessa is hosting a dinner
at the mansion tonight.

16:58.667 --> 17:01.375
Yeah. Copy that, sir.
I already sent over four more units.

17:01.458 --> 17:02.917
Thank you, I appreciate that.

17:03.833 --> 17:05.417
-Yeah.
-[cell phone beeps]

17:09.417 --> 17:10.958
[Fisk] You know, they say that

17:11.042 --> 17:13.667
driving is most dangerous after it rains.

17:16.208 --> 17:18.458
The collected oil, bits of rubber.

17:19.083 --> 17:20.792
More slippery than ice.

17:21.333 --> 17:23.833
You're not ready for it,
and you spin out of control.

17:26.292 --> 17:28.625
The things that can damage us most...

17:29.792 --> 17:32.208
are the ones
we're least prepared for, aren't they?

17:32.292 --> 17:35.208
[sighs] Shit. I-- Look, I--

17:35.292 --> 17:37.333
I should've told you sooner. I just--

17:37.792 --> 17:40.083
You know, I--
I wanted to get more information

17:40.167 --> 17:42.583
-before coming to you because I--
-Daniel, this...

17:43.458 --> 17:45.625
person is mocking me.

17:46.167 --> 17:48.875
Yes, sir. I'm sorry, sir.

17:49.875 --> 17:51.083
They found this

17:51.167 --> 17:53.708
on Commissioner Gallo's body.

17:56.333 --> 17:57.417
Fuckin' A.

17:57.500 --> 18:00.750
Do you remember
when I told you if you ever betray me...

18:02.542 --> 18:04.542
it'll be the last thing you ever did?

18:05.167 --> 18:06.667
Yeah, I do.

18:07.625 --> 18:10.125
I wouldn't. I swear, Mayor Fisk.

18:10.208 --> 18:13.917
Daniel, you are
the Deputy Mayor of Communications.

18:15.500 --> 18:17.333
-Yeah.
-Finding out how

18:17.667 --> 18:21.333
inside information is ending up in here

18:21.417 --> 18:23.292
-is your responsibility.
-Yes.

18:23.375 --> 18:25.958
-[loudly] Do we understand each other?
-Absolutely, sir.

18:26.042 --> 18:28.167
A hundred percent.
It's completely my fault--

18:28.250 --> 18:29.958
Good. I have two questions.

18:30.500 --> 18:32.667
Do you have any idea
where the leak came from?

18:33.458 --> 18:35.208
No. Honestly, sir, I don't. I--

18:35.292 --> 18:37.667
Is there anyone in this building
you need to protect?

18:37.750 --> 18:38.750
Yeah.

18:39.958 --> 18:41.208
You.

18:46.583 --> 18:47.583
Good answer.

18:52.458 --> 18:53.708
[Buck] You don't need it.

18:53.792 --> 18:54.792
You got me.

18:54.875 --> 18:59.250
And, of course, the finest security
New York taxpayers can afford.

18:59.333 --> 19:01.208
[gun cocking]

19:03.875 --> 19:07.083
Have you ever been in the same room
with Benjamin Poindexter?

19:08.792 --> 19:09.917
Not a ballroom.

19:11.333 --> 19:12.750
Up close, personal?

19:13.458 --> 19:15.125
No, ma'am.

19:16.000 --> 19:17.083
I have.

19:18.167 --> 19:19.875
[gun clicking]

19:19.958 --> 19:22.000
I wouldn't call this a need,

19:22.375 --> 19:24.708
more like a well-thought-out...

19:25.708 --> 19:26.708
want.

19:27.250 --> 19:28.250
[Buck] Hmm.

19:29.292 --> 19:30.625
[gun cocks]

19:35.250 --> 19:36.250
[gun clicks]

19:36.333 --> 19:37.333
Good choice.

19:38.833 --> 19:39.833
[Vanessa] Thank you...

19:40.667 --> 19:41.667
Buck.

19:44.333 --> 19:47.250
-[reporters speaking indistinctly]
-[people clamoring]

19:47.333 --> 19:48.333
[man] Need my help?

19:48.833 --> 19:50.417
Hey. Grab the rope.

19:52.875 --> 19:55.042
[indistinct chatter]

19:55.125 --> 19:59.167
Grab the rope, make sure to go
when they park and they dock. Come on.

19:59.250 --> 20:00.458
[chatter continues]

20:00.542 --> 20:02.292
-[woman] I don't know.
-[man] Hurry up.

20:02.375 --> 20:04.042
Hurry up, lotta cargo here.

20:04.583 --> 20:06.417
Clear out the space, too.

20:06.875 --> 20:07.875
Come here.

20:07.958 --> 20:10.875
-[reporters continue indistinctly]
-[chatter continues]

20:10.958 --> 20:12.417
[man] Hey, Bobby.

20:14.083 --> 20:15.750
[sighs] It's diapers.

20:16.500 --> 20:19.292
[chuckles] Yeah,
they weren't on the ship with me.

20:19.375 --> 20:21.208
-It's just a show.
-It's a good one.

20:21.292 --> 20:23.417
It's local salvage company. Union workers.

20:23.792 --> 20:26.000
It'd be a good headline. It's very, uh...

20:26.667 --> 20:27.875
voter-friendly.

20:30.458 --> 20:32.792
So, what happens
when they think no one's watching?

20:33.458 --> 20:35.667
[man 2] Hey, Drew, get 'em on that crane.

20:35.750 --> 20:37.875
[chatter continues]

20:56.958 --> 21:00.292
I still don't understand
why would you take such a risk

21:00.958 --> 21:02.417
on the Northern Star.

21:03.083 --> 21:04.875
I believe that I can do...

21:06.500 --> 21:08.750
more good than just New York.

21:09.375 --> 21:11.708
You have built an empire

21:11.792 --> 21:13.167
that will be remembered.

21:13.250 --> 21:15.500
Will it? New Yorkers have a short memory.

21:16.292 --> 21:17.292
But, yes, it...

21:18.292 --> 21:22.792
It's true we have built
something generational here, Vanessa.

21:23.542 --> 21:25.500
-But--
-Without an heir.

21:28.083 --> 21:30.167
We've always been enough for each other.

21:30.958 --> 21:32.042
Yes.

21:32.708 --> 21:34.333
Have you ever considered

21:35.250 --> 21:37.792
that with all that we have
and what we've done,

21:38.625 --> 21:42.125
that we're obligated to make
a global impact?

21:42.208 --> 21:43.375
[Vanessa] Hmm.

21:44.250 --> 21:46.042
How many more worlds

21:46.917 --> 21:48.333
do you need to conquer?

21:49.250 --> 21:50.292
Hmm?

21:52.917 --> 21:54.125
How many are there?

21:56.667 --> 21:58.667
[loud chatter]

22:03.583 --> 22:05.625
But those are definitely not diapers.

22:07.167 --> 22:08.167
Shit.

22:12.708 --> 22:14.333
There's Task Force everywhere.

22:14.583 --> 22:16.000
[Matt] Place is a black hole.

22:16.333 --> 22:19.333
If Fisk moves those guns
into Red Hook, they vanish.

22:20.583 --> 22:23.625
I don't think we have a choice anymore.
I gotta get into the port.

22:23.708 --> 22:24.708
No.

22:25.208 --> 22:26.583
No, Matt, it's suicide.

22:28.167 --> 22:29.583
It's our only shot at Fisk.

22:30.958 --> 22:32.208
We might not get another.

22:32.292 --> 22:33.292
Shit.

22:39.583 --> 22:40.667
I hope they find him.

22:43.250 --> 22:44.250
Me, too.

22:45.042 --> 22:46.042
He's...

22:47.292 --> 22:48.292
He's a good man.

22:49.958 --> 22:50.958
He tried.

22:57.792 --> 22:59.583
Sometimes I wonder if...

23:00.375 --> 23:04.417
If your Tío Hector would have never put on
that White Tiger mask,

23:05.292 --> 23:06.792
maybe it'd all be different.

23:06.875 --> 23:08.042
No, he had to.

23:08.750 --> 23:10.125
-It was who he was.
-[speaking Spanish]

23:12.792 --> 23:14.833
[in English] If everyone was too scared
to be a hero,

23:14.917 --> 23:15.917
we'd have none.

23:16.417 --> 23:17.417
And I'd be dead.

23:24.042 --> 23:26.333
Hey, let's get a snack.

23:29.958 --> 23:31.500
[doorbell chimes]

23:34.208 --> 23:35.292
[indistinct chatter]

23:35.375 --> 23:36.375
Hola, Berto.

23:36.750 --> 23:38.583
[boy] Sucks you gotta say that.

23:38.667 --> 23:40.375
-Come on.
-[Javi] A'ight, come on. Come on.

23:48.542 --> 23:49.542
Angela,

23:50.042 --> 23:51.167
why are you so boring?

23:51.250 --> 23:53.208
[boys laughing]

23:53.292 --> 23:54.417
Look at his shoes.

23:54.500 --> 23:57.125
Crocodile shoes.
I could hear you squeaking from outside.

23:57.208 --> 23:58.583
-Nah.
-I didn't even talk.

23:58.667 --> 24:01.208
Shut up with your
three-musketeers-from-Dollar-Tree ass.

24:01.292 --> 24:02.833
Hey, hey, put that back.

24:03.708 --> 24:05.625
[in Spanish]

24:05.708 --> 24:06.708
[chuckles]

24:08.417 --> 24:09.750
[in Spanish]

24:17.833 --> 24:20.375
-[in English] Mind your business.
-[in English] Put that back already.

24:20.458 --> 24:22.292
[all chattering in Spanish]

24:22.375 --> 24:23.792
[glass shatters]

24:25.125 --> 24:26.125
Berto...

24:27.375 --> 24:28.375
[in Spanish]

24:28.458 --> 24:29.583
[Berto in Spanish]

24:33.500 --> 24:35.167
[in English] Just put that down, okay?

24:35.250 --> 24:36.917
[Berto in Spanish]

24:37.000 --> 24:38.000
Berto.

24:40.250 --> 24:41.292
[in Spanish]

24:42.792 --> 24:43.875
[officer grunts]

24:49.292 --> 24:50.292
[boy grunts]

24:52.208 --> 24:54.583
-[Soledad] Stop. He's a kid.
-[officer] They're thieves.

24:54.667 --> 24:56.458
He's taking the law into his own hands.

24:56.542 --> 24:59.083
-Mind your business.
-Our neighborhood is our business.

24:59.542 --> 25:01.333
-[officer] Hey!
-Hey! No. Don't...

25:01.417 --> 25:02.417
[man] Come on, man!

25:02.500 --> 25:03.583
[officer 2] Hold him down.

25:08.417 --> 25:10.750
That's assaulting an officer.
You're coming with me.

25:10.833 --> 25:13.042
No! Get off of her! Son of a bitch!

25:13.125 --> 25:15.125
-Get off of her! No!
-Don't be stupid, kid.

25:15.208 --> 25:17.125
-[man 2] What are you doing?
-[man 3] Hey! Let her go!

25:17.208 --> 25:19.250
[people clamoring]

25:22.625 --> 25:23.750
Screw these guys!

25:24.375 --> 25:26.000
[man 2] Hey, what are you doing, man?

25:26.083 --> 25:28.583
-[clamoring intensifies]
-[glass shattering]

25:30.875 --> 25:32.917
[Soledad] Get home, get home,
get home, get home!

25:33.000 --> 25:35.083
It's gonna be okay. Get home!

25:35.167 --> 25:36.417
Get home, okay?

25:36.500 --> 25:38.500
No! No!

25:38.583 --> 25:41.167
Get home, please! Get home safely.

25:41.250 --> 25:43.292
-[screaming]
-No!

25:44.500 --> 25:45.500
No!

25:49.292 --> 25:51.500
[clamoring continues]

25:55.125 --> 25:56.542
[Javi] Get out of our neighborhood!

25:57.417 --> 25:59.208
Get the fuck out of our neighborhood!

26:15.917 --> 26:18.208
[Heather] A lot is said about
a person's mental health,

26:18.583 --> 26:19.708
but what about a city's?

26:20.625 --> 26:23.583
The randomness of a horrific crime.

26:24.833 --> 26:27.792
A stranger pushing another
in front of a train,

26:27.875 --> 26:30.750
a self-proclaimed artist

26:31.292 --> 26:33.250
murdering innocent people.

26:33.625 --> 26:36.875
How do we collectively heal
from these horrors?

26:38.250 --> 26:41.542
You know, you don't have to
go solo to these things.

26:41.625 --> 26:43.875
-[♪ soft music playing]
-[indistinct chatter]

26:45.083 --> 26:46.250
If I may,

26:46.333 --> 26:49.250
how did you and Mr. Murdock leave things?

26:49.333 --> 26:50.333
Not well.

26:50.417 --> 26:51.750
Matt was in a...

26:53.042 --> 26:54.042
place...

26:55.042 --> 26:56.167
before he got shot.

26:57.083 --> 27:00.542
He has very strong feelings
about your husband.

27:01.292 --> 27:02.833
Mr. Murdock

27:03.208 --> 27:06.958
always was the champion of the vigilantes.

27:07.042 --> 27:08.250
My husband...

27:10.750 --> 27:12.417
-not so much.
-[chuckles softly]

27:13.167 --> 27:14.167
Do you think

27:14.667 --> 27:16.083
Frank Castle or...

27:17.167 --> 27:19.042
Daredevil killed Matt?

27:19.125 --> 27:20.292
No, I don't.

27:23.250 --> 27:25.208
-Is my husband overworking you?
-No.

27:26.417 --> 27:27.417
Not really.

27:27.833 --> 27:30.333
-Vigilante trials are coming up, so...
-Hmm.

27:31.292 --> 27:33.875
Must be hard to get into the head of...

27:35.625 --> 27:36.708
those people?

27:37.417 --> 27:39.125
Sometimes it's a little too easy.

27:40.542 --> 27:41.708
That's the scary part.

27:52.042 --> 27:53.125
Is something wrong?

27:54.083 --> 27:55.083
No...

27:55.167 --> 27:56.208
That thing, right?

27:57.333 --> 28:00.292
That... sudden cold feeling.

28:00.375 --> 28:04.708
My gram used to say,
"That's a goose walking over your grave."

28:05.625 --> 28:07.625
-[laughs]
-[chuckles]

28:10.500 --> 28:12.292
[imperceptible]

28:23.417 --> 28:24.958
[exhales heavily]

28:25.042 --> 28:26.958
[thudding on door]

28:29.750 --> 28:31.167
[door opens]

28:33.000 --> 28:34.000
Hello?

28:53.000 --> 28:54.000
Hey.

28:59.750 --> 29:01.708
If anybody's there, I'm not playing!

29:06.208 --> 29:07.208
Angela?

29:08.750 --> 29:10.042
How did you get in here?

29:11.125 --> 29:12.583
Hey, hey, what happened?

29:15.458 --> 29:17.083
-What happened?
-They took her.

29:18.000 --> 29:19.125
They took my tía.

29:20.083 --> 29:21.750
Oh, my God. [sighs]

29:22.292 --> 29:23.792
Oh, come here, honey. I'm so--

29:24.792 --> 29:25.917
[sighs]

29:28.083 --> 29:31.333
-I'll start checking the jails, okay?
-No, that won't work.

29:31.417 --> 29:32.542
The Task Force took her,

29:32.625 --> 29:34.750
-and people usually disappear.
-Shit.

29:38.333 --> 29:39.500
-[kisses]
-[sniffles]

29:39.583 --> 29:40.625
[Kirsten sighs]

29:43.500 --> 29:44.583
That's it, isn't it?

29:46.708 --> 29:47.917
[Kirsten] Angela...

29:48.875 --> 29:50.000
Can I see it?

29:51.208 --> 29:52.333
[latch clicks]

30:00.000 --> 30:01.625
[Kirsten] Soledad didn't want it.

30:01.708 --> 30:03.542
Yeah. I'm not surprised.

30:05.625 --> 30:07.458
Hard to be a hero these days, huh?

30:13.167 --> 30:15.708
[♪ mellow music playing]

30:25.667 --> 30:28.042
I thought we were editing The BB Report.

30:28.458 --> 30:29.833
It's a working dinner.

30:31.583 --> 30:35.333
Coq au vin, pommes du moutard,
and haricots vert.

30:35.417 --> 30:37.542
-Oh! Where from?
-Me.

30:37.958 --> 30:40.333
-And Julia Child.
-[scoffs]

30:40.417 --> 30:42.750
-Bullshit.
-Oh, truth.

30:43.208 --> 30:44.583
Yeah, it's a thank-you,

30:44.667 --> 30:47.125
you know,
for gettin' the place cleaned, and...

30:47.583 --> 30:48.708
a bunch of other shit.

30:49.167 --> 30:51.708
I mean, we both know
I wouldn't have made Deputy Mayor

30:51.792 --> 30:54.083
-if it wasn't for your help.
-We helped each other.

30:54.583 --> 30:55.583
Yeah.

30:56.667 --> 30:58.208
I didn't know you could cook.

30:58.292 --> 30:59.500
I can't.

30:59.875 --> 31:03.042
But I just read the directions,
did what they said.

31:03.625 --> 31:05.208
Hopefully, it's all right.

31:06.083 --> 31:08.042
I got no clue about the wine, but it was--

31:08.125 --> 31:10.625
It was expensive, so, hopefully it's good.

31:15.208 --> 31:16.208
[chuckles softly]

31:16.292 --> 31:17.292
Shit.

31:17.542 --> 31:19.833
Daniel, this is great.

31:20.333 --> 31:21.458
-Wow.
-Good.

31:22.208 --> 31:24.583
-I'm... I'm glad you like it.
-[chuckles softly]

31:25.208 --> 31:27.208
'Cause we got some things to figure out.

31:29.917 --> 31:31.958
-[knocking on door]
-Mayor Fisk?

31:48.667 --> 31:50.167
Were you looking for me?

31:52.250 --> 31:53.708
You know what that is?

31:55.000 --> 31:56.000
Yeah.

31:56.083 --> 31:57.917
Some crazy shit.

31:58.000 --> 32:00.250
A weird mask with Daredevil on the boat?

32:03.042 --> 32:05.833
That video, it came
from inside the Mayor's office.

32:06.750 --> 32:08.417
Maybe even off my laptop.

32:09.333 --> 32:10.333
Okay.

32:12.667 --> 32:13.875
What's your question?

32:15.708 --> 32:18.000
-Don't fuck with me, BB.
-[chuckles softly]

32:18.083 --> 32:20.250
You burned me bad
with that Mayor Garbage leak.

32:20.333 --> 32:22.250
Okay. That was then, and this is now.

32:22.625 --> 32:24.292
It's not me, seriously.

32:24.375 --> 32:27.083
I get it. You're a journalist,
I'm a schmuck from Staten.

32:27.167 --> 32:28.542
-Fuck me or whatever.
-Okay.

32:28.625 --> 32:31.333
But if you are leaking stuff,
anything, stop.

32:31.875 --> 32:32.875
It's no game.

32:33.917 --> 32:35.000
You could get hurt.

32:35.583 --> 32:36.708
We could get hurt.

32:39.958 --> 32:41.667
You're scared of him, aren't you?

32:43.125 --> 32:45.250
Politics is a brutal business, isn't it?

32:53.375 --> 32:54.375
Gallo...

32:55.208 --> 32:56.292
was a good man.

32:56.708 --> 32:58.875
We didn't always see eye-to-eye, but...

33:00.375 --> 33:01.375
I'll miss him.

33:02.042 --> 33:03.958
I'm just being smart.

33:06.333 --> 33:08.167
I wouldn't blame you if you were.

33:10.583 --> 33:11.958
[exhales sharply]

33:12.042 --> 33:14.167
I mean, you had to have asked yourself,

33:14.875 --> 33:16.292
what if the rumors are true?

33:17.167 --> 33:18.208
About Gallo?

33:18.833 --> 33:20.875
-About my uncle?
-[exhales deeply]

33:21.875 --> 33:23.917
Come on, BB. I mean, look, look at this.

33:25.125 --> 33:26.250
Life is good.

33:27.667 --> 33:28.667
I don't know, like,

33:29.292 --> 33:31.333
integrity can cost.

33:32.750 --> 33:36.417
Sometimes, it's better
not to know, or to ask.

33:37.625 --> 33:39.542
You did the right thing, Miss Sheila.

33:43.583 --> 33:44.625
Can I walk you out?

33:45.542 --> 33:46.583
Yeah.

33:47.875 --> 33:49.583
If you are leaking stuff,

33:49.667 --> 33:51.208
just stop.

33:51.292 --> 33:52.292
Please.

33:55.875 --> 33:57.167
[glasses clink]

33:58.917 --> 34:00.958
This place was alive for a long time,

34:01.042 --> 34:04.750
and you three were the heart of it.

34:05.333 --> 34:06.583
I'm sorry.

34:07.583 --> 34:08.667
Shit.

34:09.500 --> 34:10.583
Maybe you're right.

34:10.667 --> 34:13.792
-[car honks in distance]
-[brakes squealing]

34:17.458 --> 34:18.542
[whispers] Josie...

34:22.417 --> 34:24.583
[car doors opening, closing]

34:27.750 --> 34:29.208
[knocking on door]

34:37.792 --> 34:39.583
-Angie?
-Josie.

34:41.417 --> 34:42.542
What's goin' on?

34:43.500 --> 34:46.417
I wanted to check up on you.
Make sure everything's all right.

34:46.500 --> 34:48.958
Maybe some people
are worried about Cherry.

34:49.417 --> 34:50.417
Don't be.

34:51.125 --> 34:52.208
He's safe.

34:53.167 --> 34:54.292
Take care.

34:54.375 --> 34:55.500
Lock your doors.

34:55.583 --> 34:56.917
Fisk is hunting.

34:57.833 --> 34:59.542
Resist. Rebel.

35:01.583 --> 35:03.583
[tape rewinding sound effect playing]

35:06.625 --> 35:08.917
-[♪ fanfare plays]
-[Mayor Kingpin] It's me again,

35:09.000 --> 35:10.250
Mayor Kingpin,

35:10.333 --> 35:14.167
here to give you a better,
more beautiful New York,

35:14.250 --> 35:17.417
without all the riffraff
messin' up our city.

35:17.500 --> 35:18.875
[people screaming]

35:19.750 --> 35:21.208
[man on speaker] You must leave.

35:22.292 --> 35:24.292
[Mayor Kingpin]
I promised you a safer city,

35:24.375 --> 35:27.292
and look at how safe I'm making it!

35:27.833 --> 35:29.625
Rounding up all the...

35:30.792 --> 35:32.875
[echoing] ...vigilantes.

35:33.750 --> 35:35.000
[maniacal laughter]

35:35.083 --> 35:36.708
Hiding in plain sight,

35:36.792 --> 35:40.792
as random people I just don't like.

35:40.875 --> 35:41.875
Don't worry,

35:42.250 --> 35:43.917
all these people are safe

35:44.000 --> 35:46.417
with all your childhood dogs

35:46.500 --> 35:48.542
in a farm upstate.

35:49.250 --> 35:50.708
And for all you rebels,

35:50.792 --> 35:53.375
the more you resist, the more you rebel,

35:53.458 --> 35:55.750
it hurts my feelings.

35:56.500 --> 35:57.625
[baby crying]

35:57.708 --> 35:59.875
There's nothing to worry about.

35:59.958 --> 36:01.458
I'm keeping you safe.

36:01.542 --> 36:04.500
Because, remember, I love you, New York.

36:04.583 --> 36:06.667
I'm Mayor Fisk, and I approve this lie--

36:06.750 --> 36:08.167
I mean, message.

36:08.583 --> 36:10.458
[heavy breathing]

37:31.458 --> 37:33.708
I know why you're hunting me.

37:39.250 --> 37:41.042
-[gun fires]
-[gasping]

37:45.333 --> 37:46.333
You okay?

37:46.875 --> 37:47.875
Are you okay?

37:49.708 --> 37:52.083
-I'm here.
-[breathing heavily]

37:53.417 --> 37:55.250
I can't get you into Red Hook.

37:57.000 --> 37:58.333
You were right. It's a...

37:59.667 --> 38:00.833
It's a black hole.

38:03.625 --> 38:04.750
There has to be a way.

38:05.792 --> 38:06.792
Well...

38:07.333 --> 38:09.292
I'd prefer one where you get out alive.

38:11.417 --> 38:12.417
Yeah, me, too.

38:16.167 --> 38:17.208
[Fisk] It's okay.

38:17.292 --> 38:18.875
It's going to be okay, my love.

38:19.208 --> 38:20.292
What's on your mind?

38:25.417 --> 38:27.333
[Vanessa] I hope that one day,

38:27.417 --> 38:29.875
we find everything we want.

38:31.208 --> 38:32.792
Someplace peaceful.

38:33.542 --> 38:35.083
And where would that place be?

38:36.000 --> 38:37.375
New York is our home.

38:37.792 --> 38:38.792
No.

38:39.958 --> 38:41.500
You are my home.

38:42.000 --> 38:43.708
[Karen] You ever think we'd end up here?

38:44.250 --> 38:45.417
There are worse places.

38:46.792 --> 38:47.792
Like Brooklyn?

38:47.875 --> 38:50.542
[both laughing]

38:51.667 --> 38:52.708
That's--

38:52.792 --> 38:54.292
-I liked Brooklyn.
-Oh, yeah?

38:54.375 --> 38:55.708
My place was nice.

38:56.125 --> 38:57.708
[Vanessa] We still own the island.

38:58.833 --> 38:59.833
Yes.

39:00.125 --> 39:02.000
When was the last time we were there?

39:02.708 --> 39:05.542
I hate the feeling of sand
between my toes.

39:05.625 --> 39:07.250
[laughing]

39:08.625 --> 39:10.125
I did like it there, though.

39:11.625 --> 39:12.625
Anywhere with you.

39:13.667 --> 39:14.708
[Vanessa] Mmm.

39:14.792 --> 39:18.292
Do you really think that
we could live-- Thrive...

39:20.625 --> 39:21.958
outside of all this?

39:22.375 --> 39:23.375
I do.

39:25.125 --> 39:26.208
I have to.

39:30.042 --> 39:31.208
[softly] I have to.

39:33.125 --> 39:34.708
[Matt] I do miss my records, though.

39:34.792 --> 39:36.042
Hold that thought.

39:37.333 --> 39:38.750
No-- Wait. Oh!

39:38.833 --> 39:40.625
-[Karen] Mmm-mmm.
-[sighs]

39:40.708 --> 39:42.375
[♪ R&B music playing on speakers]

39:42.458 --> 39:43.500
What are you doing?

39:46.500 --> 39:47.500
Oh!

39:47.583 --> 39:49.792
[laughs] No way!

39:50.292 --> 39:51.958
Vive le resistance.

39:52.042 --> 39:53.083
[laughs]

39:57.625 --> 39:59.708
♪ In the fire ♪

40:01.125 --> 40:03.792
♪ It was burning ♪

40:04.708 --> 40:07.542
♪ Sweetheart, I know... ♪

40:08.625 --> 40:11.917
-[vehicles approaching]
-[distant thudding]

40:12.875 --> 40:13.875
Hold on.

40:15.875 --> 40:17.250
[officer on speakers] On my mark.

40:17.333 --> 40:18.917
-[high-pitched ringing]
-[Matt groaning]

40:19.000 --> 40:21.625
-This is the Anti-Vigilante Task Force.
-Hey.

40:21.708 --> 40:24.708
We have you surrounded.
Come out or we'll be forced to remove you.

40:24.792 --> 40:26.167
-[officer 2] Go!
-[officer 3] Hands up!

40:26.250 --> 40:27.792
[Josie] Get off of me!

40:27.875 --> 40:29.167
[Matt] They have Josie. Stay here.

40:29.250 --> 40:30.333
-Stay low!
-[Karen] Yeah, go.

40:31.125 --> 40:32.667
[sirens wailing]

40:32.750 --> 40:35.958
[officer 1] Vigilantism will not
be tolerated in this city.

40:36.917 --> 40:39.583
-This is the Anti-Vigilante Task Force.
-[Josie] All right.

40:39.667 --> 40:42.917
We have you surrounded.
Come out or we'll be forced to remove you.

40:43.000 --> 40:44.208
[Daredevil grunting]

40:44.292 --> 40:46.917
-Any and all resistance will be--
-[high-pitched ringing]

40:48.125 --> 40:49.417
Go somewhere safe.

40:52.042 --> 40:53.500
[officer 4] Clear every floor!

40:56.375 --> 40:57.375
-[Karen] Hey.
-Hey, hey, hey.

40:57.458 --> 40:59.083
[grunting]

41:00.792 --> 41:02.833
[all grunting]

41:10.750 --> 41:12.833
[♪ music continues playing]

41:19.542 --> 41:21.875
-[Daredevil yelling]
-[all grunting]

41:56.583 --> 41:58.333
[panting]

41:58.417 --> 41:59.875
[sirens wailing]

42:01.792 --> 42:02.792
Karen!

42:04.125 --> 42:05.250
Karen!

42:05.333 --> 42:07.375
[continues panting]

42:10.042 --> 42:11.750
Karen!

42:44.875 --> 42:46.708
[Karen sighs]

42:46.792 --> 42:49.167
-[Daredevil] Where were you?
-I know. I know. Just...

42:49.708 --> 42:50.917
-Come on.
-What happened?

42:51.958 --> 42:53.417
I have something to show you.

43:15.125 --> 43:16.125
What did you do?

43:17.208 --> 43:18.375
They're hunting us.

43:19.417 --> 43:21.292
Maybe it's time we started hunting them.

43:22.292 --> 43:23.833
[Daredevil breathing heavily]
